The paper deals with association rule mining, which is a common topic in data mining and machine learning. The focus is on pruning the resulting rules to avoid redundancy and subsumption, which is a problem often encountered in this field. Therefore, cs.DB (databases) and cs.AI (artificial intelligence) are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes a new definition of redundancy and subsumption based on confidence and support, which is related to machine learning and data analysis, making cs.LG (machine learning) a likely category as well. The paper also deals with analyzing and improving performance, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
